WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:35.958
Subtitle Provide by dramacool.asia Translator [Admin.@YNG]

00:00:49.674 --> 00:00:52.552
Focus on what you're doing, Yuzuha!

00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:12.113
It's okay, Dad.

00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:22.499
I'm gonna survive.

00:02:52.505 --> 00:02:55.925
SHIBUYA STATION

00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:18.698
What?

00:03:54.984 --> 00:03:56.027
How did it go?

00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:57.737
Not good. Ugh, I got nothing.

00:03:58.738 --> 00:03:59.614
All right.

00:04:00.114 --> 00:04:02.742
Let's just grab anything
that might be useful.

00:04:14.587 --> 00:04:16.881
FURNITURE AND INTERIOR GOODS FLOOR

00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:18.508
Just as I thought,

00:04:18.591 --> 00:04:20.802
all the IC chips have been destroyed.

00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:25.306
Video cameras, digital clocks.

00:04:25.890 --> 00:04:28.268
Anything that operates
with an electronic circuit board

00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:29.602
isn't gonna work.

00:04:32.063 --> 00:04:34.274
But old stuff like this still works,

00:04:34.857 --> 00:04:37.277
since none of it has any IC chips.

00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:41.281
What does that mean?

00:04:43.032 --> 00:04:44.867
It might mean…

00:04:45.827 --> 00:04:46.869
Hurry!

00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:48.746
Look, fireworks!

00:04:53.459 --> 00:04:55.753
An electromagnetic pulse attack.

00:04:57.463 --> 00:04:59.507
I read about this online.

00:04:59.590 --> 00:05:01.551
When inserted into the stratosphere,

00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:05.680
it's a weapon capable of destroying
the electronics in an entire city.

00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:08.057
Seriously?

00:05:13.646 --> 00:05:16.399
So… why is this working?

00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:20.028
No idea.

00:05:22.447 --> 00:05:23.448
VISA
RYOHEI ARISU

00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:24.449
REMAINING DAYS: 3

00:05:25.199 --> 00:05:26.284
Hey!

00:05:38.671 --> 00:05:41.174
It's completely useless
if we can't charge it.

00:05:46.596 --> 00:05:48.806
This place looks safe enough.

00:05:57.648 --> 00:05:59.734
All right. This might be a good weapon.

00:06:00.902 --> 00:06:03.237
What do you need a weapon for?

00:06:05.448 --> 00:06:06.532
Zombies.

00:06:11.913 --> 00:06:13.873
You know you can't use
electricity or gas, right?

00:06:14.499 --> 00:06:16.292
But I can still use the portable stove.

00:06:16.376 --> 00:06:18.669
It has batteries
that I can also use in my flashlight.

00:06:18.753 --> 00:06:20.505
And I like a hot meal sometimes.

00:06:21.964 --> 00:06:22.924
Hmm.

00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:46.614
This is so good!

00:06:47.782 --> 00:06:49.575
Ah, nice and hot!

00:06:49.659 --> 00:06:51.702
We haven't eaten anything
since yesterday.

00:06:54.622 --> 00:06:57.125
Hey, what were you guys doing

00:06:57.208 --> 00:06:58.751
when everyone disappeared?

00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:02.004
Bathroom.

00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:04.465
We were all in the same stall.

00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:06.884
Why were you all in the same stall?

00:07:07.468 --> 00:07:08.386
Where were you?

00:07:13.558 --> 00:07:14.767
Saori…

00:07:24.068 --> 00:07:25.153
I was at work.

00:07:26.529 --> 00:07:29.323
I was in the conference room
doing some paperwork.

00:07:30.074 --> 00:07:31.159
And then,

00:07:31.784 --> 00:07:33.744
everyone in the office disappeared.

00:07:34.704 --> 00:07:37.457
Did you happen to see or hear
anything at all?

00:07:56.851 --> 00:07:57.810
Boss?

00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:16.037
Not really.

00:08:17.788 --> 00:08:19.582
I came to this place three days ago,

00:08:20.791 --> 00:08:24.212
and I was forced to play this game,
just like all of you were.

00:08:26.047 --> 00:08:28.424
Everybody died, except for me.

00:08:31.135 --> 00:08:32.845
You mean, you used them as bait, right?

00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:34.514
Think whatever you want.

00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:37.350
All I wanted…

00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:40.436
was to survive.

00:08:51.572 --> 00:08:52.740
Well…

00:09:00.414 --> 00:09:01.874
What kind of game was it?

00:09:05.294 --> 00:09:06.796
It was at the subway.

00:09:08.923 --> 00:09:10.883
They used poisonous gas in the game.

00:09:13.761 --> 00:09:15.137
Everyone was vomiting blood.

00:09:16.806 --> 00:09:18.516
Blood was coming out of their eyes.

00:09:23.312 --> 00:09:24.355
Weird, huh?

00:09:26.190 --> 00:09:28.150
The day everyone disappeared.

00:09:28.234 --> 00:09:29.902
It was yesterday for the three of us.

00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:30.987
Yeah.

00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:33.030
But it was three days ago for her.

00:09:33.114 --> 00:09:34.365
Why the time difference?

00:09:35.032 --> 00:09:35.866
That's right.

00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:38.244
And those vegetables that were rotten…

00:09:38.953 --> 00:09:41.080
They take longer than a few days
to go bad.

00:09:41.872 --> 00:09:43.207
What's going on?

00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:47.086
Maybe the speed of time is…

00:09:47.628 --> 00:09:49.088
different from the normal world?

00:09:49.797 --> 00:09:50.631
Huh?

00:09:51.424 --> 00:09:53.175
I don't really know, but…

00:09:53.884 --> 00:09:56.596
Take the, the four of us here.

00:09:57.305 --> 00:10:01.309
The timeline of when people disappeared
is different, like you said.

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:07.940
Did we time travel while we were
in the subway bathroom stall?

00:10:08.024 --> 00:10:09.525
There's no way.

00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:11.485
There's also no way
people just disappeared.

00:10:11.569 --> 00:10:12.778
Time travel isn't real.

00:10:12.862 --> 00:10:14.614
Then explain the game
and people disappearing.

00:10:14.697 --> 00:10:16.115
I don't know, all right?

00:10:16.198 --> 00:10:17.491
Anyways,

00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:20.119
one thing we know for sure
about this game…

00:10:21.871 --> 00:10:23.664
A game master's running it.

00:10:24.332 --> 00:10:25.458
Game master?

00:10:26.250 --> 00:10:27.918
Someone came up with this game.

00:10:28.586 --> 00:10:29.837
That's for sure.

00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.799
So while we're in a bathroom stall,

00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:36.218
they get rid of everyone in Tokyo

00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:37.762
and set up this game?

00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:39.305
They keep track of our movements…

00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:43.893
…and fire lasers through our heads
when we make the wrong move.

00:10:45.394 --> 00:10:47.688
What kind of person would do that?

00:10:48.814 --> 00:10:50.483
I don't know, but it's definitely possible

00:10:50.566 --> 00:10:52.860
if they inserted
a highly accurate GPS microchip

00:10:52.943 --> 00:10:54.028
into our bodies.

00:10:54.111 --> 00:10:56.656
Spoken like a real IT geek.

00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:59.867
But who the hell could be
behind this thing?

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:01.160
Hmm.

00:11:01.243 --> 00:11:02.453
Could it be…

00:11:02.953 --> 00:11:06.040
some government-run experiment
or something?

00:11:08.125 --> 00:11:10.878
There were some rumors
going around at my work.

00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:14.632
An IT company from Europe wanted
to conduct an experiment.

00:11:14.715 --> 00:11:16.509
They'd established a VR space,

00:11:16.592 --> 00:11:19.720
then created an alternate world
identical to the real one.

00:11:22.932 --> 00:11:25.768
But we should be able to tell VR
from the real world.

00:11:26.977 --> 00:11:28.479
Man…

00:11:28.562 --> 00:11:29.939
This hurts.

00:11:31.482 --> 00:11:33.442
I don't think
VR can cause burns like that.

00:11:35.903 --> 00:11:38.114
Maybe it's God.

00:11:38.197 --> 00:11:40.533
This has to be the work of God.

00:11:40.616 --> 00:11:42.743
Otherwise, how else do you explain it?

00:11:42.827 --> 00:11:44.829
You're talking crazy now.

00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:46.997
No, man. I think…

00:11:47.873 --> 00:11:49.333
God really does exist.

00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:56.215
Hey, is it getting worse?

00:11:58.634 --> 00:11:59.885
It's all right.

00:11:59.969 --> 00:12:01.011
Oh, it's gonna be fine.

00:12:08.686 --> 00:12:10.938
I think we gotta get Chota
to a doctor.

00:12:13.232 --> 00:12:14.692
You know how he is.

00:12:15.317 --> 00:12:17.194
It's probably hurting more than he says.

00:12:17.695 --> 00:12:18.696
But it's getting to him.

00:12:22.450 --> 00:12:23.409
Arisu.

00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:27.538
Let's get in the game tomorrow night,

00:12:27.621 --> 00:12:28.706
just you and me.

00:12:29.707 --> 00:12:30.624
What?

00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:33.836
But we've got three days left
on our visas.

00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.841
It's better to get in the game
while we still have time.

00:12:40.259 --> 00:12:41.802
I just don't think

00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:45.598
Chota's gonna be able to make it through.
He's in too much pain.

00:12:52.813 --> 00:12:54.023
How are you doing?

00:12:55.024 --> 00:12:56.150
Not bad, thanks.

00:12:57.610 --> 00:13:00.571
If the two of us don't figure out
how to get through this game,

00:13:00.654 --> 00:13:02.281
we won't be able to protect Chota.

00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:05.159
You're right, but…

00:13:06.827 --> 00:13:08.204
Maybe we can find a doctor too.

00:13:08.704 --> 00:13:10.498
We'll meet more people if we're playing.

00:13:12.583 --> 00:13:14.460
Do we really have to play again?

00:13:15.085 --> 00:13:17.129
Maybe we'll get an idea
what this game's about.

00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:23.969
Yeah, I guess.

00:13:25.012 --> 00:13:26.138
If we play,

00:13:26.222 --> 00:13:28.015
we might find out their signature.

00:13:29.975 --> 00:13:31.101
Signature?

00:13:32.061 --> 00:13:34.104
Yeah. If someone actually created
this game,

00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:39.068
there's a kind of signature they use,
like formatting.

00:13:39.985 --> 00:13:41.111
If we can discover that,

00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:43.989
we might be able to figure out
a strategy for the game.

